			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have been wanting and saving pp for this sword since lvl 16.  Thought about doing the quest but was too low to have much confidence in whether I would be able to pull together a group to help me.  Seems kinda unfair that the recommended lvl to attempt this quest is high 20s when the sword starts proc at lvl 20.  But I have read about groups in the low 20 banding together to quest for this item.  The posts always indicated that it takes a long time and some of the drops are almost impossible to get in a timely manner.  I don't belong to a guild so it is hard to hold a group together for 2 hours much less 2 days.  So, I determined that the only way I would acquire one anytime soon would be by purchase.  Most sellers were asking anywhere from 400pp to 650pp on Vazaelle.  My balance in the bank was only 250pp in coin with some various hard assets such as emergency armor and weapons.  I have been logging on every morning before work to look for someone wanting to unload one cheap (everything is cheaper in the a.m., if you can find it).  After one week of talking to people day and night wanting fair prices but more than I could afford I was stunned to see this morning someone auctioning for 300pp.  Still more than I had but closer.  I offered 250pp and bless his soul he accepted.  Now I am only lvl 18 so the thing doesn't proc yet but that gives me time to raise my skill in 1 hand slash and bash which I have been ignoring for the past 5 levels in using a 2 hand Charred TulWar.  So, to all you aspiring Paladins that think the Ghoulbane is beyond you reach don't despair.  Just keep &quot;Auction&quot; on and pray that a generous seller will accept your offer.  Bless Chigger's kind hearted rogue soul for selling me this weapon.  Good luck to all.
				</font>
			</td>

